main event: An unidentified object was tracked by ground radar for approximately 20 minutes on August 1, 1956.
interesting points: The object was traveling at a speed of 300-400 mph,The object was at an altitude of 5,000-10,000 feet,The individual's reports indicated the object was a bright yellow color,The sighting involved at least two observers who corroborated information,The object was noted to sway as though moved by wind.
witness description: Two observers provided consistent details about the sighting.
